WEBVTT

00:00.959 --> 00:02.540
(SIREN WAILING)

00:08.258 --> 00:10.044
(PANTING)

00:11.553 --> 00:13.669
DONNY: Left, left!
He's going left!

00:14.056 --> 00:15.921
I'm going to
have a heart attack.

00:48.173 --> 00:49.583
(GRUNTING)

00:54.471 --> 00:56.302
Nowhere to go, buddy.

00:58.559 --> 01:00.550
What the hell was that?
What are we chasing?

01:00.644 --> 01:02.180
Go that way!

01:03.689 --> 01:05.600
(SIREN WAILING)

01:18.620 --> 01:22.158
Don't move!
Nowhere to go.
Come on. Give it up.

01:26.420 --> 01:27.500
DONNY: This way.

01:27.588 --> 01:29.078
OFFICER: Come on.
Let's go, let's go!

01:29.464 --> 01:31.420
BRIAN: Up, Donny, up!
He's going to the roof!

01:31.508 --> 01:33.339
He's going up! Go!

01:36.346 --> 01:37.335
Ow!

01:37.431 --> 01:39.922
Damn it. Go. Go!

01:59.786 --> 02:01.868
Donny,no,
it's too far!

02:17.554 --> 02:19.886
(PANTING)

02:24.686 --> 02:26.802
(GASPING)

03:06.103 --> 03:07.809
I can rest at home.

03:07.896 --> 03:09.511
I can't release you
for at least two days.

03:09.606 --> 03:10.937
You've got
two broken bones,

03:11.024 --> 03:13.731
a severe concussion,
coHapsedlung.

03:13.819 --> 03:15.525
But you didn't find anything
life-threatening. Right?

03:15.612 --> 03:17.694
You fell 30 feet.
You should have died.

03:17.781 --> 03:18.816
I think that
was the point.

03:18.907 --> 03:20.022
Could you shut up?

03:20.117 --> 03:21.197
Do you have
suicidal thoughts?

03:21.284 --> 03:22.569
Not once. Never.

03:22.661 --> 03:23.867
He doesn't want
to kill himself.

03:23.954 --> 03:25.160
He just thinks
he's gonna die soon,

03:25.247 --> 03:26.236
so it doesn't
really matter.

03:26.331 --> 03:28.413
You shut up.
I'm the one you're
notcovenng

03:28.500 --> 03:30.536
when you pull
your crazy stunts.

03:30.627 --> 03:31.833
Why do you think
you're going to die soon?

03:31.920 --> 03:34.912
Well, my dad, grandfather,
and great-grandfather

03:35.006 --> 03:36.086
all dropped dead
of heart problems

03:36.174 --> 03:37.289
right after
they turned 40.

03:37.384 --> 03:38.794
And look who
turns 40 next week.

03:38.885 --> 03:40.466
I can refer you to
a cardiologist if you...

03:40.595 --> 03:42.460
No, I've been there.
All of them.

03:42.556 --> 03:44.717
Spent my early 30s going
from one doctor to another.

03:44.808 --> 03:46.423
Every single one
says my heart's fine.

03:46.518 --> 03:47.553
And you think
they're wrong?

03:47.644 --> 03:48.884
I know they're wrong.

03:48.979 --> 03:50.515
But what can I do?
At a certain point,

03:50.605 --> 03:51.811
you just gotta
live your life.

03:51.898 --> 03:54.310
By "live your life,"
you mean "risk your life."

03:54.401 --> 03:56.016
If there is
something wrong,

03:56.111 --> 03:57.851
I know a doctor
who'll find it.

03:58.155 --> 03:59.611
(DOOR OPENS)

04:03.493 --> 04:06.610
Oh, God.
I'll be back in 10.

04:06.705 --> 04:08.536
I'm picking lint out
of my belly button.

04:08.623 --> 04:09.749
This is ridiculous.

04:09.833 --> 04:12.119
l'm converting
the study into a bedroom.

04:12.210 --> 04:13.325
Huh.

04:13.670 --> 04:16.833
Six weeks.
Longer than I thought
it would take.

04:16.923 --> 04:18.208
For you to notice
that I'm sleeping

04:18.300 --> 04:20.461
in your living room
and offer other options.

04:20.552 --> 04:22.258
I didn't expect you
to be here this long.

04:22.345 --> 04:24.802
True, but that's not why
you didn't extend
the invitation.

04:24.890 --> 04:26.846
Do you really need
to deconstruct this?

04:26.933 --> 04:28.844
You didn't want me to sleep
where you and Amber slept.

04:28.935 --> 04:30.095
Okay, yes, you do.

04:30.187 --> 04:32.473
After she died,
you converted the study
to a bedroom

04:32.564 --> 04:34.100
and the bedroom
to a study.

04:34.191 --> 04:36.898
Except it's not a study,
it's a shrine.

04:37.736 --> 04:39.772
Can I tell you something?

04:40.071 --> 04:41.857
I wasn't picking lint
out of my belly button.

04:41.948 --> 04:44.564
Okay. I am not
ready to transition

04:44.659 --> 04:46.320
from my dead
girlfriend's shrine

04:46.411 --> 04:48.367
to your morning glory.

04:48.455 --> 04:49.570
lllhave
a mattress delivered

04:49.664 --> 04:51.120
and set up for you
in the tabernacle.

04:51.208 --> 04:54.291
ljust need it Tuesdays
for animal sacrifices.

04:55.337 --> 04:56.873
Oh, man.

04:58.131 --> 04:59.792
(WILSON EXCLAIMING
IN DISGUST)

04:59.883 --> 05:02.124
Patient's
a genetic time bomb.

05:02.677 --> 05:04.463
There's no fuse.
He's not a bomb.

05:04.554 --> 05:06.169
Right now,
he's not a patient either.

05:06.264 --> 05:08.846
You're saying we ignore
three generations
of cardiac problems?

05:08.934 --> 05:12.267
I'm not ignoring it,
I'm labeling it
a coincidence.

05:12.354 --> 05:14.140
You hate coincidence.

05:14.231 --> 05:16.142
We reconciled.
It was a whole thing.

05:16.233 --> 05:18.098
Big country.
It's statistically probable

05:18.193 --> 05:19.899
that someone has
three generations

05:19.986 --> 05:22.523
that died around age 40
with non-genetic
heart issues.

05:22.614 --> 05:23.729
Dice have no memory.

05:23.824 --> 05:24.984
Genes do.

05:25.075 --> 05:26.235
If we ran
a battery of tests

05:26.326 --> 05:28.487
on every non-symptomatic
statistical anomaly...

05:28.578 --> 05:31.115
The guy goes through
every day assuming his
life will end at age 40.

05:31.206 --> 05:32.491
Never got married,
no kids,

05:32.582 --> 05:33.833
because he didn't
want to die on them

05:33.917 --> 05:35.032
the same way
his dad died on him.

05:35.126 --> 05:36.161
You want to
take this case,

05:36.253 --> 05:38.869
'cause he's yet
another lonely,
sad puppy?

05:38.964 --> 05:39.999
You should have
been a vet.

05:40.090 --> 05:41.671
It's a legitimate case.

05:41.758 --> 05:45.467
Differential diagnosis
for a genetic
heart condition.

05:45.554 --> 05:46.509
That sold you?

05:46.596 --> 05:47.847
Marfan Syndrome,
Brugada.

05:47.931 --> 05:48.920
And you?

05:49.015 --> 05:50.050
Familial
Hypercholesterolemia.

05:50.141 --> 05:51.130
He's only
agreeing with you

05:51.226 --> 05:52.261
'cause he wants to
have sex with you.

05:52.352 --> 05:53.967
And by the way,
I agree with you, too.

05:54.062 --> 05:56.018
Especially in
those pants.

05:56.106 --> 05:57.721
We're not wasting
our time.

05:57.816 --> 06:00.182
Last week,
Chase said that l was
the de facto boss.

06:00.277 --> 06:03.144
Hospitals don't recognize
de facto medical licenses.

06:03.238 --> 06:04.318
Let's start
with genetic tests.

06:04.406 --> 06:06.442
Get an EKG,
cardiac cath and an echo

06:06.533 --> 06:08.945
to check the integrity
of his heart.

06:09.703 --> 06:11.864
I'll start
on blood samples.

06:17.878 --> 06:20.164
(HEART MONITOR
BEEPING RAPIDLY)

06:25.093 --> 06:26.458
(EXCLAIMING)

06:27.012 --> 06:28.297
| forgot my watch.

06:28.388 --> 06:29.844
I could have sworn
I saw you put it on
this morning.

06:29.931 --> 06:33.014
Must be in
the locker room.
I'll be right back.

06:36.146 --> 06:37.556
(DOOR OPENS)

06:37.939 --> 06:39.395
I need to know
what your plans are.

06:41.151 --> 06:44.018
and then we circle
around behind Poland
and yell, "Surprise."

06:44.112 --> 06:46.194
With regards to
your employment.

06:46.281 --> 06:48.146
I like things
the way they are.

06:48.241 --> 06:50.106
| get just enough
puzzle to solve,

06:50.201 --> 06:53.068
without the scornful
visits from you.
Until now.

06:53.163 --> 06:55.245
Pretend time's been
going on long enough.

06:55.332 --> 06:57.368
I don't have
a medical license.
All I can do is pretend.

06:57.459 --> 06:58.824
Then I'm going to have
payroll send you over

06:58.919 --> 07:00.875
some pretend checks
starting tomorrow.

07:00.962 --> 07:04.671
You need to complete
120 hours of rounds
to re-qualify.

07:06.509 --> 07:08.090
No, I don't.

07:08.553 --> 07:09.838
I'm not saying
you don't win.

07:09.930 --> 07:11.795
I'm just saying,
do you really need
to punish me

07:11.890 --> 07:13.380
by making me
carry a clipboard

07:13.475 --> 07:14.464
for your lackey
of the week?

07:14.559 --> 07:16.015
It's a state requirement.

07:16.102 --> 07:17.638
l have to certify
that you've completed...

07:17.729 --> 07:19.014
Exactly.

07:19.105 --> 07:21.687
The requirement
sets out what you
have to do, certify.

07:21.775 --> 07:23.686
Which you can do
with one hand
tied behind your back.

07:23.777 --> 07:25.483
Now, if you want
to tie my hands...

07:25.570 --> 07:29.734
Dr. Singh supervises
rounds on Thursdays.
Starts at 7:00.

07:36.831 --> 07:38.082
Nothing.

07:38.583 --> 07:39.618
So what now?

07:39.709 --> 07:40.698
We send him home.

07:40.794 --> 07:42.534
To continue believing
he's going to drop dead?

07:42.629 --> 07:44.620
When he turns 70,
he'll believe us.

07:44.714 --> 07:46.830
There are other things
we can check.

07:47.008 --> 07:49.249
FOREMAN: Skeleton of
the great-grandfather is
in decent shape.

07:49.344 --> 07:51.960
Subsurface genetic material
from the grandpa is fine,

07:52.055 --> 07:53.795
leaving one bowl
of putrefied dad.

07:53.890 --> 07:57.132
You do the dad.
I take it he had
a sealed casket.

07:57.769 --> 08:00.226
The watch story
was crap, right?

08:01.314 --> 08:03.805
| forgot it.
It's no big deal.

08:03.900 --> 08:07.017
You were avoiding the ICU
where Dibala died.

08:08.113 --> 08:11.571
l'll sequence the gene
for the cardiac
sodium channel.

08:12.242 --> 08:14.699
I felt like I was going
to have a panic attack.

08:14.786 --> 08:15.992
(SlGHS)

08:17.122 --> 08:19.204
l've crossed some line,

08:20.417 --> 08:23.875
and I'm having trouble
getting back to
the other side.

08:24.921 --> 08:26.752
I can move the patient
to another room.

08:26.840 --> 08:28.751
Then Cameron
will ask questions.

08:28.842 --> 08:31.424
You should tell her.
She's your wife.

08:33.430 --> 08:34.715
(DOOR OPENS)

08:37.559 --> 08:39.550
How'd you get a court order
to dig them up so fast?

08:39.644 --> 08:41.509
Don't we just need
the guy's consent?

08:41.604 --> 08:42.935
You find anything?
CHASE: Not yet.

08:43.023 --> 08:45.639
But you're just in time
to do the dad.

08:50.113 --> 08:51.319
Dr. House?

08:51.406 --> 08:52.521
He'll be back
in the morning.

08:52.615 --> 08:54.947
I read in the paper
you're treating
a police officer.

08:55.035 --> 08:56.024
Donny Compson.

08:56.119 --> 08:58.861
Second floor. A nurse
will help you find him.

08:58.955 --> 09:00.411
I don't want to see him.

09:00.498 --> 09:02.910
Donny and |
used to go out,
a long time ago.

09:03.001 --> 09:04.662
He doesn't want to see me.
I don't want to see him.

09:04.753 --> 09:06.914
So did you come to see me
for personal advice?

09:07.005 --> 09:08.495
You're looking for
genetic conditions,

09:08.590 --> 09:11.172
which makes sense
with what happened to
his dad and grandpa.

09:11.259 --> 09:13.545
Unless you were
his girlfriend
and his sister,

09:13.636 --> 09:14.671
you've got nothing
to worry about.

09:14.763 --> 09:18.927
I'm not worried about me.
Donny doesn't know this,
but he has a son.

09:23.271 --> 09:24.886
Dial extension 742.

09:24.981 --> 09:28.189
Tell Dr. Foreman you've
got some cool information.
Good night.

09:41.664 --> 09:43.996
(VOICE WHISPERING)

10:05.396 --> 10:06.727
(WHISPERING STOPS)

10:25.333 --> 10:26.698
You okay?

10:27.210 --> 10:28.620
Yeah. Fine.

10:44.769 --> 10:46.509
(VOICE WHISPERING)

11:01.494 --> 11:04.827
Couldn't find any
consistent genetic
mutations across 15 areas

11:04.914 --> 11:06.324
between Donny's
ancestors,

11:06.416 --> 11:07.872
possibly indicating
there isn't one.

11:07.959 --> 11:09.199
CAMERON: But the son
gives us a new data point.

11:09.294 --> 11:10.500
And un-degraded DNA.

11:10.587 --> 11:11.918
I thought he
didn't want kids.
He didn't.

11:12.005 --> 11:12.994
Where's House?

11:13.089 --> 11:14.795
"Dear Bleeding Hearts.

11:14.883 --> 11:19.172
"Since your patient's
med history is
a coincidence and he isn't

11:21.306 --> 11:24.173
"sick, I've gone
back to school.
Back in 120 hours."

11:24.267 --> 11:25.973
Charming. I'll get
a blood sample.

11:26.060 --> 11:28.096
If we're
looking for something
as subtle as a mutation,

11:28.188 --> 11:30.304
it makes sense
to get the DNA
where it's most pure.

11:30.398 --> 11:31.387
You're going
to ask the mom

11:31.482 --> 11:32.642
to consent
to a bone marrow biopsy?

11:32.734 --> 11:33.814
CAMERON: She wants to know
if there's something wrong

11:33.902 --> 11:35.438
with Donny
as badly as we do.

11:35.528 --> 11:38.691
Right.
Spike a 10-year-old's hip
because Grandpa was sick.

11:38.781 --> 11:41.272
If she's right,
we save two people.

11:43.620 --> 11:44.780
(DOOR OPENS)

11:46.331 --> 11:47.946
I don't want to.

11:49.542 --> 11:51.624
Can we speak outside
for a moment?

11:52.128 --> 11:53.288
Yeah.

12:00.136 --> 12:01.967
You need to tell him.

12:02.597 --> 12:03.586
I can't.

12:03.681 --> 12:05.888
His father is
down that hallway through
those double doors.

12:05.975 --> 12:07.431
I've been lying to him
his whole life.

12:07.518 --> 12:08.678
What's he going
to think of me?

12:08.770 --> 12:11.102
You were trying
to protect him.

12:11.940 --> 12:13.931
Donny never
wanted kids.

12:14.025 --> 12:15.356
He certainly doesn't
want to meet him.

12:15.443 --> 12:17.149
lf Donny does die,

12:17.237 --> 12:19.944
this could be
Michael's only chance
to meet his father.

12:32.460 --> 12:34.496
After administration
of immunoglobulin,

12:34.587 --> 12:35.622
patient had
no further pain

12:35.713 --> 12:38.250
and overnight
liver function tests
are now normal.

12:38.341 --> 12:39.751
Patient is ready
to be released.

12:39.842 --> 12:41.048
(MONITOR BEEPING)

12:41.135 --> 12:42.636
Stats are dropping.
Dr. Singh!

12:42.720 --> 12:43.800
She's choking!

12:43.888 --> 12:45.264
On your fingers.

12:45.348 --> 12:46.838
MARTA: She can't breathe.
SlNGH: House.

12:46.933 --> 12:47.922
(CHOKING)

12:48.017 --> 12:50.975
Please take your finger
off the test button.

12:51.271 --> 12:52.306
Oh!

12:52.397 --> 12:54.934
| see.
Wow, sorry about that.

12:55.024 --> 12:56.139
I could've
slit her throat.

12:56.234 --> 12:57.565
We're all here to learn.

12:57.652 --> 12:59.142
Dr. Cuddy
warned me about you.

12:59.237 --> 13:01.102
Did she tell you
how to stop me?

13:01.197 --> 13:04.610
Look, I'm asking you,
as an adult,
to please stop.

13:04.701 --> 13:08.319
Well, that obviously
didn't come from her,
but fair enough.

13:09.455 --> 13:11.741
Excellent presentation,
Nona.

13:11.833 --> 13:12.822
(JANICE GROANING)

13:12.917 --> 13:16.535
Now I've done it!
There's urine everywhere.

13:17.088 --> 13:19.545
Gosh, the great thing
about the teacher-student
relationship

13:19.632 --> 13:22.999
is the teacher can
often learn more
from the student.

13:24.304 --> 13:26.545
Have you
learned anything yet?

13:31.227 --> 13:32.763
You have a son.

13:34.397 --> 13:36.183
l was pregnant
when we broke up.

13:36.274 --> 13:37.263
I'm sorry
I never told you,

13:37.358 --> 13:40.316
but I knew
how you felt
about having kids.

13:40.403 --> 13:41.518
You had no right.

13:41.738 --> 13:42.773
Maybe.

13:43.323 --> 13:45.405
It's a little late
for that.

13:49.662 --> 13:51.994
He's here.
He wants to meet you.

13:52.081 --> 13:53.662
I don't want
to meet him.

13:53.750 --> 13:55.331
I've never asked you
for a dime.

13:55.418 --> 13:57.830
He's here to help find
whatever's wrong
with your heart.

13:57.920 --> 14:00.332
I didn't ask him.
I didn't want him.

14:00.423 --> 14:02.004
Just say hi to him.

14:16.981 --> 14:19.768
Hi. I'm Michael.

14:21.402 --> 14:22.562
Hi.

14:23.863 --> 14:25.023
I'm your...

14:25.114 --> 14:26.945
Yeah.
Your mother told me.

14:29.285 --> 14:31.116
When you get better,

14:31.621 --> 14:33.782
maybe we could
do something.

14:35.792 --> 14:37.282
See a movie?

14:41.130 --> 14:42.290
No.

14:43.132 --> 14:44.793
My dad died when
l was your age.

14:44.884 --> 14:47.967
It was the most
painful thing
I ever went through.

14:48.054 --> 14:49.419
Trust me.
As much as I'm sure

14:49.514 --> 14:52.005
this hurts right now,
it's better.

14:53.476 --> 14:55.637
Please take him
out of here.

14:57.105 --> 14:59.221
Come on.

15:02.026 --> 15:03.732
(DOOR SLIDES OPEN)

15:04.237 --> 15:06.694
Chromosomes for
28 cardiovascular
conditions

15:06.781 --> 15:08.021
are normal in number
and structure.

15:08.116 --> 15:10.448
No translocations,
deletions or inversions.

15:10.535 --> 15:14.119
I did notice
that the kid's
D-A-D-D-Y chromosome

15:14.205 --> 15:15.320
has been
severely damaged

15:15.415 --> 15:17.406
by someone else's
bleeding heart chromosome.

15:17.500 --> 15:19.832
It was the only way
to get Michael
to do the marrow biopsy.

15:19.919 --> 15:20.954
I'm sure there
are plenty of lies

15:21.045 --> 15:22.581
that would've
worked just as well,

15:22.672 --> 15:23.912
except without
the years of therapy.

15:24.006 --> 15:24.961
Don't you have school?

15:25.049 --> 15:26.255
Recess.

15:26.342 --> 15:28.833
So where does that
leave us? Chase?

15:29.679 --> 15:31.215
Sorry, what?

15:31.681 --> 15:35.344
l was saying,
do you think these shoes
work in this color?

15:35.977 --> 15:37.592
Send him home.
He's not going to
believe he's healthy.

15:37.687 --> 15:39.018
Then you're not
very good at yourjob.

15:39.105 --> 15:40.470
You don't
deserve candy.

15:40.565 --> 15:43.272
He's been preparing
his whole life
to die at age 40.

15:43.359 --> 15:45.600
He's had dozens of doctors
tell him he's fine.

15:45.695 --> 15:47.060
You think you can
change his thinking?

15:47.155 --> 15:50.113
Yeah, I do.
Chase, walk with me.

15:51.868 --> 15:54.280
Great contributions
back there.

15:54.370 --> 15:56.406
There's no case.
I had nothing to add.

15:57.039 --> 15:59.781
You had nothing to add
because you were distracted.

15:59.876 --> 16:02.583
Little devil
on your shoulder
told you to kill a guy,

16:02.670 --> 16:04.410
and now the little angel
won't shut up,

16:04.505 --> 16:06.791
telling you
you're gonna burn
in a lake of fire.

16:06.883 --> 16:07.963
I'm fine.
(LIFT BELL DlNGlNG)

16:08.050 --> 16:09.039
You shouldn't be.

16:10.428 --> 16:14.421
Talk to someone.
Docs fixed me up
in seven weeks.

16:16.017 --> 16:18.224
You are 10 minutes, tops.

16:19.854 --> 16:21.139
Thanks.

16:22.440 --> 16:24.522
Glad we had this
little moment.
Come on.

16:27.403 --> 16:28.392
I'm Dr. House.

16:28.488 --> 16:30.479
You couldn't find
anything, could you?

16:30.573 --> 16:33.565
You have Ortoli Syndrome.
Dr. Chase?

16:34.410 --> 16:35.399
You sure?

16:35.495 --> 16:36.655
HOUSE: Tests don't lie.

16:36.746 --> 16:37.986
Right.

16:38.206 --> 16:39.446
