these discharge papers,

17:45.439 --> 17:47.054
lngetyou
a bottle of meds.

17:47.149 --> 17:48.889
Take one twice a day
for a week,

17:48.985 --> 17:51.226
you'll live a long,
heathlWe.

18:12.717 --> 18:14.127
(VOICE WHISPERING)

18:14.760 --> 18:15.795
(WHISPERING STOPS)

18:19.140 --> 18:20.550
(BANGING ON DOOR)

18:26.689 --> 18:30.022
WILSON:
Answer the door, House.
It's gotta be for you.

18:30.109 --> 18:31.440
Are you watching TV?

18:31.527 --> 18:32.687
It's the door!

18:32.778 --> 18:34.234
(BANGING CONTINUES)

18:37.658 --> 18:38.773
Were you on the phone?
No.

18:38.868 --> 18:39.948
Just now,
were you talking?

18:40.036 --> 18:41.742
No, I'm alone.

18:42.288 --> 18:43.949
You okay, House?

18:47.126 --> 18:48.787
Why are you here?

18:49.462 --> 18:53.296
Donny collapsed four hours
after we discharged him.
He's dead.

19:01.891 --> 19:04.758
His apartment manager
found him on the floor
in the laundry room.

19:04.852 --> 19:06.888
He said
he wasn't breathing.

19:06.979 --> 19:09.095
He called the EMTs,
but it was too late.

19:10.274 --> 19:12.890
I sent the guy home
with mints.

19:12.985 --> 19:14.441
Whatever it is,
we all missed it.

19:15.071 --> 19:18.734
Yeah. I missed the fact
that there was something
to miss.

19:19.825 --> 19:21.941
What is wrong with me?

19:22.036 --> 19:23.321
You had good reason.

19:24.080 --> 19:25.536
Patient presented
with no symptoms,

19:25.623 --> 19:28.535
and all his tests
came back negative.

19:29.085 --> 19:31.622
What's the official
cause of death?

19:31.712 --> 19:33.543
Autopsy hasn't
been performed yet.

19:33.798 --> 19:36.380
EMTs brought him
to General,

19:36.467 --> 19:37.877
but I requested
they ship him back

19:37.968 --> 19:40.675
to our morgue
for the post-mortem.

19:42.765 --> 19:44.005
Good.

19:47.353 --> 19:49.184
Hon? Wake up.

19:53.150 --> 19:55.892
Why are you dressed?
You can't sleep?

19:55.986 --> 19:58.068
I want to go tell Cheryl
that Donny died.

20:00.157 --> 20:01.363
It's 4:00 in the morning.

20:01.450 --> 20:03.031
They're nearly
two hours away.

20:03.119 --> 20:04.825
I figure by the time
I get there,
she'll be awake.

20:04.912 --> 20:08.120
Babe, come back to bed.
Call her in a few hours.

20:09.709 --> 20:13.167
It's the sort of thing
she needs to hear
face-to-face.

20:19.593 --> 20:21.299
Is everything okay?

20:22.012 --> 20:23.968
Everything's fine. Why?

20:24.056 --> 20:25.921
Last week,
I understood

20:26.016 --> 20:27.881
that you were stressed out
about the Dibala M&M,

20:27.977 --> 20:32.391
and I gave you your space.
But that's over now,
and you're still acting...

20:35.443 --> 20:37.308
I'm worried about you.

20:38.654 --> 20:40.895
Don't be. I'm fine.

20:42.491 --> 20:43.822
Really.

20:44.326 --> 20:46.738
And you'd tell me
if you weren't?

20:48.205 --> 20:49.536
Promise?

20:51.167 --> 20:52.282
Yeah.

20:53.461 --> 20:54.621
Okay.

20:57.840 --> 20:59.000
Hey.

21:00.259 --> 21:02.124
I love you.

21:02.344 --> 21:03.504
I love you, too.

21:07.850 --> 21:09.010
(DOOR OPENS)

21:12.396 --> 21:14.808
Donny Compson, age 39.

21:32.041 --> 21:33.997
(DRILL WHIRRING)

21:35.878 --> 21:38.164
Can we cut
to the money shot?

21:38.255 --> 21:40.962
It's his heart,
so let's look at his heart.

21:41.050 --> 21:42.790
Nice Y-incision.

21:43.552 --> 21:46.339
You can't perform an autopsy
without a medical license.

21:46.430 --> 21:48.045
Really?

21:48.140 --> 21:49.801
Because I don't think
there's anything
I can screw up

21:49.892 --> 21:52.383
that we haven't
already screwed up.

21:58.734 --> 22:00.144
Opening
post-mortem incision,

22:00.236 --> 22:01.817
beginning at the mid-line
of the sternum.

22:01.904 --> 22:03.485
(DRILL WHIRRING)

22:11.539 --> 22:12.779
(DRILL STOPS)

22:14.124 --> 22:18.242
That's odd.
It almost looks
like he's bleeding.

22:23.759 --> 22:26.216
(SCREAMING)

22:27.847 --> 22:29.678
(CHOKING)

22:31.976 --> 22:35.264
I think the autopsy's
gonna have to wait
a little bit.

22:39.400 --> 22:41.436
FOREMAN:
He was briefly conscious,

22:41.527 --> 22:44.064
then his
systolic dipped below 60
and he was out again.

22:44.154 --> 22:46.691
Differential diagnosis
for resurrection. Go.

22:46.782 --> 22:47.897
Obviously,
he wasn't dead.

22:47.992 --> 22:49.778
His heart slowed enough
that the EMTs could think...

22:49.869 --> 22:51.359
Yes, the fact that
he's not dead

22:51.453 --> 22:52.909
means we did
absolutely nothing wrong.

22:52.997 --> 22:54.328
CAMERON: There are several
documented cases

22:54.415 --> 22:56.747
where tetrodotoxin ingestion
caused apparent death.

22:56.834 --> 22:58.665
It wasn't something he ate,
it's something he already had.

22:58.752 --> 23:00.583
And his dad,
and his grandpa, and...

23:00.671 --> 23:03.583
Extreme bradycardia
could be caused by
sick sinus syndrome.

23:03.674 --> 23:04.754
CHASE: Sinoatrial block.

23:04.842 --> 23:06.798
What if it's
not his heart?

23:07.303 --> 23:10.841
Let's work from
the tenuous assumption
that we're not idiots.

23:10.931 --> 23:14.219
You spent days
examining a heart
up, down, and sideways,

23:14.310 --> 23:17.393
declaring it healthy
just a few hours before
it basically shut down.

23:17.479 --> 23:20.642
So we need to think
about causes in places
you didn't look.

23:20.733 --> 23:23.065
(VOICE WHISPERING)

23:23.152 --> 23:24.858
CHASE: Could be metabolic.

23:25.988 --> 23:27.273
You okay?

23:27.364 --> 23:28.774
(CHATTERING)

23:30.075 --> 23:31.235
Yeah.

23:31.827 --> 23:35.240
What about
a genetic predisposition
to an autoimmune disease?

23:35.331 --> 23:37.947
Isolated Anti-Ro
Antibody could cause
complete heart block.

23:38.042 --> 23:39.907
Could also be passed
through four generations.

23:40.002 --> 23:42.744
Autoimmune it is.
Start him on steroids.

23:48.177 --> 23:50.714
Hey. How are you feeling?

23:52.348 --> 23:54.930
My whole head
is killing me.

23:55.017 --> 23:56.882
You just came through
a severe trauma.

23:58.062 --> 23:59.848
What do you remember?

24:03.567 --> 24:06.525
l was changing my laundry
over to the dryer.

24:07.863 --> 24:10.070
That's it?
You were declared dead.

24:10.157 --> 24:12.068
You made it
all the way to autopsy.

24:12.242 --> 24:13.618
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

24:13.702 --> 24:15.283
My jaw aches.

24:16.580 --> 24:19.572
And obviously,
I don't have
Ortoli Syndrome.

24:20.584 --> 24:21.744
It's hard to
get too excited

24:21.835 --> 24:23.211
about coming back
from the dead

24:23.295 --> 24:27.379
when anything I do,
anything you give me,
it all ends the same way.

24:36.934 --> 24:38.049
(BEEPING)

24:42.773 --> 24:44.183
Outer and middle ear
respond well.

24:44.274 --> 24:46.356
Hearing thresholds
are normal
at all frequencies.

24:46.443 --> 24:47.603
Eardrum is
perfectly healthy.

24:47.695 --> 24:49.356
What if I...

24:49.780 --> 24:51.691
What if I sometimes
hear whispering?

24:51.782 --> 24:54.899
Then you're
probably hearing
someone whispering.

24:55.577 --> 24:56.908
I had some
dental work done

24:56.996 --> 24:58.236
in the Philippines
when l was a kid.

24:58.330 --> 25:01.697
Adjoining metal fillings
could corrode and
pick up AM radio signals.

25:01.792 --> 25:03.328
Open your mouth.

25:05.462 --> 25:07.453
Your fillings
don't touch.

25:08.966 --> 25:10.877
So there's no reason for me
to be hearing things?

25:10.968 --> 25:13.004
I can only tell you that
you're hearing sounds
as you should.

25:13.095 --> 25:14.505
If you're also
hearing sounds
that you shouldn't,

25:14.596 --> 25:15.756
that would be
a psychosis.

25:15.848 --> 25:18.965
You'd have to talk to
someone who does brain.
I only do ears.

25:27.943 --> 25:32.858
Bravo.
It's amazing how you did
120 hours in one day.

25:33.657 --> 25:37.241
I wasn't on
my best behavior,
I admit. Allow me.

25:38.996 --> 25:41.612
From now on,
I'm gonna supervise your
practicum requirements.

25:41.707 --> 25:42.822
That won't be necessary.

25:42.916 --> 25:44.907
You want to annoy
another doctor first?
Eventually...

25:45.002 --> 25:48.790
It's not necessary
because I'm not ready
to be a doctor again.

25:51.675 --> 25:53.085
I'm sorry.

25:56.096 --> 25:57.302
(DOOR OPENS)

25:57.973 --> 25:59.304
(DOOR OPENS)

26:11.070 --> 26:12.310
(SlGHS)

26:13.155 --> 26:14.520
Are you sleeping out here?

26:14.615 --> 26:16.947
| just dozed off
in front of the TV.

26:17.034 --> 26:18.820
With bedding?
Maybe.

26:19.787 --> 26:22.870
I can't sleep in there,
the heater's screwed up.

26:23.916 --> 26:26.532
If you need to talk,
if you need more help...

26:26.627 --> 26:28.163
I'm just tired.

26:29.213 --> 26:30.669
...l'm right here.

26:30.756 --> 26:33.839
Great.
Can you be right here
somewhere else?

26:41.141 --> 26:44.929
Myjaw still hurts.
My tooth, actually. A lot.

26:45.020 --> 26:47.102
I'm sorry,
you're maxed out
on your pain meds.

26:47.189 --> 26:48.804
Try to sleep.

26:49.149 --> 26:50.605
(DOOR OPENS)

26:50.692 --> 26:51.818
(DOOR CLOSES)

26:51.902 --> 26:52.891
(GROANING)

27:13.757 --> 27:15.793
Dentist looked
at the tooth
the guy pulled out.

27:15.884 --> 27:17.624
There was nothing
wrong with it.

27:17.719 --> 27:20.301
So aside from
him being an idiot,
what else did we learn?

27:20.389 --> 27:23.256
The pain is real.
It's coming
from somewhere.

27:23.350 --> 27:24.851
What about bone cancer?

27:24.935 --> 27:27.142
You can't connect
bone cancer
to the heart.

27:27.229 --> 27:29.060
House figure
this can wait
till the morning?

27:29.148 --> 27:31.810
Actually, he told Cuddy
he's not ready to work.

27:31.900 --> 27:33.891
He quit?
Apparently.

27:33.986 --> 27:36.602
It's a power play.
He'll be back tomorrow.

27:36.697 --> 27:39.484
Bone cancer could trigger
a paraneoplastic syndrome,

27:39.575 --> 27:40.564
which shuts down
the heart.

27:40.659 --> 27:43.116
Primary bone cancer
isn't hereditary.

27:43.203 --> 27:44.192
Li-Fraumeni Syndrome.

27:44.288 --> 27:45.653
lt's hereditary
and it increases

27:45.747 --> 27:48.614
a person's risk of
having bone cancer.

27:50.627 --> 27:51.912
You have another theory?

27:52.004 --> 27:54.461
My theory is
it's not bone cancer.

27:55.340 --> 27:58.127
Gamma survey would
locate the tumors.

28:38.884 --> 28:40.966
(VOICE WHISPERING)

29:12.084 --> 29:13.620
(WILSON SlGHS)

29:14.253 --> 29:18.713
I had pea soup today.
You'd love my breath
right now.

29:19.258 --> 29:24.002
I didn't get
a chance to run tonight.
House is having issues.

29:26.515 --> 29:28.506
I missed you
a lot today.

29:29.768 --> 29:31.508
All I wanna do is...

29:33.021 --> 29:34.761
(WILSON SIGHING)

29:34.856 --> 29:36.107
You know.

29:40.988 --> 29:43.946
No cancers on the
lateral cuneiform bone.

29:44.032 --> 29:45.772
Navicular's also clean.

29:46.451 --> 29:48.237
Chase is lying to me.

29:49.288 --> 29:52.075
And I know you know.
Tell me what's
going on, please.

29:52.165 --> 29:54.121
I'm going to tell you
the same thing I told him.

29:54.209 --> 29:56.370
Talk to your spouse.

30:03.260 --> 30:04.716
No breakfast?

30:05.220 --> 30:06.721
Not today.

30:07.389 --> 30:09.050
l'm hallucinating.

30:12.519 --> 30:13.474
What happened?

30:13.562 --> 30:15.553
It's nothing visual
this time.

30:16.565 --> 30:18.226
I hear whispering.

30:18.817 --> 30:21.308
Is that why you've
been acting so weird?
Is that why you quit?

30:21.403 --> 30:22.893
I'm losing it.

30:23.488 --> 30:25.194
I'm sure there's
a rational explanation,

30:25.282 --> 30:26.988
the wind,
a neighbor's TV...

30:27.075 --> 30:28.155
I checked everything.

30:28.243 --> 30:32.361
What's really scary is
that I hear whispering
while not on Vicodin.

30:34.082 --> 30:37.040
I'm gonna check myself
back in to Mayfield.

30:39.171 --> 30:40.251
Okay.

30:43.550 --> 30:44.665
Okay?

30:46.845 --> 30:49.382
You don't think
there might be
a logical explanation?

30:49.473 --> 30:50.508
Something I missed?

30:50.599 --> 30:51.930
You're the smartest
guy I know.

30:52.017 --> 30:54.679
If you haven't
thought of it,
it doesn't exist.

30:54.770 --> 30:58.308
l'll drive you over.
I just need to
make some tea first.

31:01.777 --> 31:03.108
You know.

31:04.446 --> 31:06.528
That you're an ass? Yeah.

31:06.615 --> 31:09.652
You overheard me talking
to my dead girlfriend
and thought to yourself,

31:09.743 --> 31:12.029
"Hmm. What kind of fun
can I have with this?"

31:12.120 --> 31:13.235
Why are you
talking to her?

31:13.330 --> 31:14.570
Did you run out
of living people?

31:14.664 --> 31:16.700
You can talk to me,
I'm right here.

31:16.792 --> 31:19.204
I miss her.
Talking to her
makes me feel better.

31:19.294 --> 31:20.579
You don't.

31:24.049 --> 31:26.381
Patient,
Lauren Maybaum, 27,

31:26.468 --> 31:29.301
presented two days ago
with severe abdominal pain.

31:29.596 --> 31:30.927
Sorry I'm late.

31:31.014 --> 31:32.129
Yesterday, you said
you weren't ready.

31:32.224 --> 31:34.215
Yesterday, lwasn't.
Today, I am.

31:34.309 --> 31:37.392
And tomorrow?
Is it possible for me to
get a five-day forecast?

31:37.479 --> 31:39.344
Feeling much better,
thank you for not asking.

31:39.439 --> 31:42.852
Either you did
have a problem,
which I can't ignore,

31:42.943 --> 31:45.605
or you were
jerking me around,
which I can't ignore.

31:45.695 --> 31:47.560
You are a woman,
you can do anything.

31:47.656 --> 31:50.693
For example, I can talk
to you outside.

31:54.162 --> 31:56.494
You sure you're
only one woman?

32:00.085 --> 32:02.622
This is the part where
you play the employee
and | play the boss.

32:02.712 --> 32:04.418
I can see your nipples.
Your turn.

32:04.506 --> 32:05.746
These kids are...

32:05.841 --> 32:07.627
No wonder
she hates him.

32:07.717 --> 32:10.254
Mmm. That's not hate.
lt's foreplay.

32:10.345 --> 32:11.505
lt's inappropriate.

32:12.514 --> 32:14.004
(WHISTLING)

32:15.225 --> 32:17.090
Gamma survey
revealed no tumors.

32:17.185 --> 32:19.392
So it's not bone cancer.

32:19.479 --> 32:20.594
Where's Chase?

32:20.689 --> 32:21.804
Don't know.

32:22.232 --> 32:23.267
Hmm.

32:23.358 --> 32:26.521
Two mysteries, cool.
Theones?

32:29.531 --> 32:33.115
Did I come in too soon?
Okay. I'm going to
take another lap,

32:33.201 --> 32:35.613
and I want three new ideas
by the time I come back.

32:35.704 --> 32:37.865
One of them's got
to be not stupid.

32:41.918 --> 32:45.410
Where there's pain,
there's nerves.

32:46.548 --> 32:49.506
Hereditary Sensory
Autonomic Neuropathy,
type 1.

32:49.593 --> 32:51.333
Miscommunication
in the brain stem

32:51.428 --> 32:53.009
mistakes nerve pain
for tooth pain.

32:53.096 --> 32:54.336
That explains
the bradycardia, too.

32:54.431 --> 32:56.171
And I like the word
"hereditary" in the title.

32:56.266 --> 32:57.847
Carbamazepine fixes him.

32:57.893 --> 32:59.804
I'll get him started
on the medication.
HOUSE: No.

32:59.895 --> 33:02.682
Chase specifically
asked if he could do it.

33:05.692 --> 33:06.898
(THUDDING)

33:08.945 --> 33:10.446
Sleep at home.

33:11.406 --> 33:12.987
So I didn't do
the gamma survey.

33:13.074 --> 33:14.280
Was it bone cancer?

33:14.367 --> 33:15.356
No.

33:15.452 --> 33:17.443
Then you should
congratulate me for
not wasting your time.

33:17.537 --> 33:19.152
Are you getting
some help,

33:19.247 --> 33:21.829
or is this the way
things are gonna be
from now on?

33:21.917 --> 33:23.498
What's pathetic is

33:23.585 --> 33:27.203
you haven't gotten help
because you want
to feel bad.

33:27.839 --> 33:29.454
You want to suffer.

33:29.549 --> 33:32.666
Because if you feel guilty,
then you're not a psychopath.

33:32.761 --> 33:34.501
Paﬂentneeds
some carbamazepine.

33:34.596 --> 33:37.759
Now I don't care
how much that room
scares you,

33:37.849 --> 33:39.134
you're doing yourjob.

33:49.444 --> 33:51.435
(MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY)

33:54.115 --> 33:57.278
How long before you cross
this one off the list?

33:59.246 --> 34:00.782
Couple of hours.

34:04.626 --> 34:06.412
You ever shoot anyone?

34:06.711 --> 34:07.791
Twice.

34:08.838 --> 34:10.624
You ever kill anyone?

34:11.341 --> 34:14.504
No. But I know
a few guys who did,
though.

34:15.095 --> 34:16.505
Did they ever
get over it?

34:16.596 --> 34:19.178
A captain I know compares it
to taking out the trash.

34:19.266 --> 34:21.006
Like it's nothing.

34:21.518 --> 34:23.054
Other hand,
I got an ex-partner

34:23.144 --> 34:25.351
who nearly drank
himself into oblivion.

34:26.481 --> 34:27.516
Did he get help?

34:27.732 --> 34:28.767
Yeah.

34:29.734 --> 34:31.349
Help didn't help.

34:37.325 --> 34:38.531
Oh, God!

34:38.994 --> 34:40.109
What is it?

34:40.787 --> 34:42.823
I went to the bathroom.

34:49.296 --> 34:50.581
Patient's lost
bowel control.

34:50.672 --> 34:52.412
Means we were
wrong about HSAN

34:52.507 --> 34:54.008
and means he's
getting worse, fast.

34:54.092 --> 34:57.004
Wouldn't want to
be the duty nurse
assigned to his floor.

34:57.095 --> 34:59.336
Get it? "Doody" nurse?

35:00.432 --> 35:01.512
Fine, do the doctor thing.

35:01.600 --> 35:02.965
CHASE: An autoimmune
disorder could explain...

35:03.059 --> 35:05.436
We put him on steroids,
he didn't respond.
It's not autoimmune.

35:05.520 --> 35:06.726
Could be Wilson's Disease.

35:06.813 --> 35:08.599
Disease that advanced
would've hit the liver.

35:08.690 --> 35:12.774
It is possible
the liver is so far gone,
the labs look normal.

35:12.861 --> 35:14.977
It's worth a shot.

35:15.071 --> 35:16.686
Go treat
with penicillamine.

35:18.158 --> 35:19.773
And when he
doesn't get better,
come back quickly,

35:19.868 --> 35:22.280
so we can get one
more shot at it.

35:26.958 --> 35:29.495
Bless me, Father,
for l have sinned.

35:31.588 --> 35:32.919
(EXHALES)

35:35.133 --> 35:36.873
FATHER PRANGE:
Take your time.

35:38.970 --> 35:41.131
How long has it been
since your last confession?

35:41.222 --> 35:42.723
I killed a man.

35:44.100 --> 35:45.180
Oh.

35:45.685 --> 35:48.062
But it was
the right thing to do.

35:48.897 --> 35:52.560
Who lives or dies
is not your decision
to make.

35:53.652 --> 35:56.894
Sometimes in
the operating room,
it feels like it.

35:57.405 --> 35:58.815
I'm a doctor.

35:59.658 --> 36:02.320
Well, then you
should know more
than anybody

36:02.410 --> 36:04.401
that every
human life is sacred.

36:05.789 --> 36:07.245
VVhy?

36:07.332 --> 36:09.744
Tell me what's sacred
about a dictator

36:09.834 --> 36:12.826
that kills
hundreds of thousands
of his own people.

36:12.921 --> 36:16.129
What is sacred
about a doctor
who kills a patient?

36:19.636 --> 36:20.842
(SCOFFS)

36:20.929 --> 36:23.341
ls itjust
the slippery slope
you're worried about?

36:23.431 --> 36:25.763
Afraid that forgiving me
for killing

36:25.850 --> 36:28.466
the worst person on earth
sets a bad precedent?

36:29.729 --> 36:32.596
I promise,
I won't tell anyone.

36:39.989 --> 36:41.604
Just forgive me.

36:42.617 --> 36:46.201
Saying 1O Hail Marys
isn't going to
do you any good.

36:46.788 --> 36:48.870
Then what do l have to do?

36:49.624 --> 36:52.536
What does God
need me to do?

36:52.627 --> 36:54.242
You can't
have absolution

36:54.337 --> 36:56.498
without first
taking responsibility.

36:57.215 --> 36:59.547
You have to turn yourself
in to the police.

36:59.634 --> 37:03.422
What, and...
And go to jail for
the rest of my life?

37:03.513 --> 37:05.469
What's just about that?

37:08.017 --> 37:10.178
I did the right thing.

37:11.104 --> 37:12.935
There has to
be another way.

37:13.022 --> 37:16.059
You want absolution,
I told you how to get it.

37:38.965 --> 37:41.172
Send this in to
the State Licensing Board.

37:41.259 --> 37:43.625
l've signed off
on all your hours.

37:44.429 --> 37:45.418
VVhy?

37:45.513 --> 37:47.344
Because it's easier
this way.

37:47.432 --> 37:49.138
You're uncomfortable
with me.

37:49.476 --> 37:50.556
No.

37:51.603 --> 37:52.934
Going by the book
was pointless.

37:53.021 --> 37:54.010
You were gonna
learn nothing.

37:54.105 --> 37:56.437
Good.
I thought it was because
of the sexual tension.

37:56.524 --> 37:57.604
There was
no sexual tension.

37:57.692 --> 37:58.681
There was tension.

37:58.777 --> 38:01.814
And it made me
feel funny, so...

38:02.989 --> 38:04.149
Here.

38:07.702 --> 38:09.112
It's too bad.

38:09.204 --> 38:13.368
l was kind of
getting into the whole
"hot for teacher" thing.

38:13.625 --> 38:15.456
You sure you're okay?

38:16.127 --> 38:17.833
Yeah. False alarm.

38:20.757 --> 38:22.213
What about us?

38:23.218 --> 38:25.459
We're good.
Just like this.

38:25.553 --> 38:26.884
You press my buttons,
| press yours.

38:26.971 --> 38:28.962
By”buﬂonsﬂ
you mean...

38:35.021 --> 38:36.136
Huh.

38:43.154 --> 38:45.236
You do make me
feel funny.

38:53.248 --> 38:55.034
You're not gonna die.

38:55.458 --> 38:57.619
l've accepted it.
It's okay.

38:59.254 --> 39:01.791
In addition to
high arches

39:01.881 --> 39:04.372
and some crystal bowl
in the shape of a tuna,

39:04.467 --> 39:08.085
you also inherited
a self-destruct button.

39:09.639 --> 39:11.129
Forms in the brain stem.

39:11.224 --> 39:13.465
Technically,
it's an aneurysm,
presses on nerves

39:13.560 --> 39:16.552
that control everything
from tooth pain
to heart rate.

39:16.646 --> 39:18.477
As you get older,
it gets bigger,

39:18.565 --> 39:23.150
until finally the button,
which I'll call
"intracranial berry aneurysm,"

39:23.236 --> 39:26.694
because I had a friend in
high school with that name,
stops the signal

39:26.781 --> 39:29.568
from your brain to
your heart and bam!

39:30.618 --> 39:32.825
How do I know you're
not still lying to me?

39:32.912 --> 39:34.573
Saying l'm healthy
just to make me
feel better?

39:34.664 --> 39:36.700
It does sound
that way, doesn't it?

39:36.791 --> 39:38.747
But this time,
no sugar pills.

39:38.835 --> 39:40.200
I'm going to cut
into your brain

39:40.295 --> 39:41.910
to make you think
that I'm fixing it.

39:42.005 --> 39:44.496
And if our fake tests
confirm it,

39:44.591 --> 39:46.377
I'm going to be cutting
into your son's brain, too.

39:46.467 --> 39:48.958
Because I'm just
that committed.

39:49.053 --> 39:51.169
Michael is going to
be okay?

39:52.265 --> 39:54.506
Unless he walks out of here
and gets run over by a bus,

39:54.601 --> 39:57.889
in which case,
lwill reconsider
your fate argument.

39:59.272 --> 40:03.515
You wanna give him a call?
Visiting hours don't
apply to my patients.

40:04.360 --> 40:06.396
Yeah. In a bit.

40:07.780 --> 40:10.613
Yeah, that's what I thought.

40:11.868 --> 40:14.860
The "saving the kid
from pain" stuff was crap.

40:14.954 --> 40:16.865
You just don't want
anything in your life
that won't let you do

40:16.956 --> 40:18.071
whatever the hell
you want to do

40:18.166 --> 40:20.157
whenever the hell
you want to do it.

40:20.251 --> 40:23.539
You've had it easy.
Sorry to screw you up.

40:42.148 --> 40:43.433
Mom.

41:00.083 --> 41:02.369
Maybe when
we get out of here...

41:06.214 --> 41:08.375
What kind of movies
you like?

41:16.557 --> 41:22.393
He's been missing
for eight hours.
Robert Chase. C-H-A-S...

41:22.730 --> 41:23.936
Hey!

41:26.234 --> 41:28.771
Never mind.
He just walked in. Sorry.

41:28.861 --> 41:29.850
You could've called me.

41:30.738 --> 41:32.194
| forgot.
To call me?

41:32.281 --> 41:34.988
It's 2:00 in the morning.
Where were you?

41:35.076 --> 41:36.407
You're drunk.

41:36.494 --> 41:37.654
All right, I...

41:39.372 --> 41:41.784
I needed to get wasted.
I did.

41:42.375 --> 41:44.206
And now I'm better.

41:44.961 --> 41:46.417
What aren't
you telling me?

41:46.504 --> 41:47.744
Nothing.

41:56.806 --> 41:58.922
(VOICE WHISPERING)

42:00.309 --> 42:01.765
(WHISPERING STOPS)

42:33.217 --> 42:34.627
Hi, Dad.

42:39.932 --> 42:41.388
I think I've been

42:42.935 --> 42:45.472
focusing on
the wrong thing.

42:47.940 --> 42:50.147
There were
some good times.

42:54.655 --> 42:57.442
Wilson, this is stupid!

43:00.244 --> 43:01.654
You see?

43:02.497 --> 43:04.738
He really is
getting better.
